              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 114,
              "href": "https://medium.com/hci-design-at-uw/information-wars-a-window-into-the-alternative-media-ecosystem-a1347f32fd8f#.qd316slbt",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 71,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 288,
              "href": "https://uxdesign.cc/the-real-state-of-power-is-culture-41dfe172b27e#.35azqp3sd",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 258,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 288,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 258,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "b74311b16ae_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2bb3",
          "text": "What we need is a science of cultural change that separates wheat from chaff — enabling those of us working in support of healthy communities and the living systems on which they depend to see through the smoke and mirrors. I have called this culture design and have written about it here, here, here, and here. In short, it is an approach that applies the tools of cultural evolution, complexity science, and the cognitive/behavioral sciences to social change as it emerges in real time.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 289,
              "href": "https://www.slideshare.net/joebrewer31/tools-for-culture-design",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 284,
              "title": "",
